{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Wood Ox|kanji=乙丑|romaji=kinoto ushi|onyomi=otsuchū|p=yǐchǒu|w=i-ch'ou|mi=i²¹ ʈʂʰoʊ̯²¹|y=jyut6 cau2|j=jyut6 cau2|ci=jyt̚ tsʰɐu̯²|mc=ʔit tʂʰjuwX|oc-bs=Ɂik ʈʰuʔ}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}} '''Yin Wood Ox also known as <!--please transliterate all the hiragana readings into romaji and provide the kanji--> Kinoto-Ushi''' (乙丑, きのとうし, おつぼくのうし, いっちゅう) is one of the combinations of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|12=draft|12=draft}}.
It is the second combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Wood Rat|ja|甲子|12=draft|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Fire Tiger|ja|丙寅|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft}}乙 represents Yin Wood, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a relationship of {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=conquest|12=draft|12=draft}} (Wood conquers Earth).
It is the second in the cycle, preceded by [[甲子]] (Kinoe-ne) and followed by [[丙寅]] (Hinoe-tora). In the [[Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory]], the [[Heavenly Stem]] [[乙]] represents the yin aspect of [[Wood]], while the [[Earthly Branch]] [[丑]] represents the yin aspect of [[Earth]]. This results in a [[Mutual Conquest]] relationship ([[Wood Conquers Earth]]).
