It is the second combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Wood Rat|ja|甲子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Fire Tiger|ja|丙寅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}乙 represents Yin Wood, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a relationship of {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=conquest|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Wood conquers Earth).
