== Months of Kinoto-Ushi == The twelfth month (December) of Gregorian calendar years ending in 3 or 8 (Heavenly Stems 癸 or 戊) corresponds to Kinoto-Ushi months. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Solar terms|ja|二十四節気|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (from {{ill|Shōkan|ja|小寒|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to the day before {{ill|Risshun|ja|立春|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) in traditional contexts.
== Days of Kinoto-Ushi == === Calendar Annotations === Days of Kinoto-Ushi are associated with the following annotations in the {{ill|Japanese calendar|ja|暦注下段|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}: * {{ill|Kyoueibi|ja|凶会日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – applicable in the 3rd and 10th lunar months. * {{ill|Gokubi|ja|五墓日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – applies to individuals whose {{ill|Na-in|ja|納音|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} corresponds to the Wood element. * {{ill|Shinkichinichi|ja|神吉日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – auspicious for spiritual matters. == See Also == * {{prefix}} * {{intitle}} {{citation needed|Wood Ox}}
