{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Wood Ox|kanji=乙丑|romaji=kinoto ushi|onyomi=otsuchū|p=yǐchǒu|w=i-ch'ou|mi=i²¹ ʈʂʰoʊ̯²¹|y=jyut6 cau2|j=jyut6 cau2|ci=jyt̚ tsʰɐu̯²|mc=ʔit tʂʰjuwX|oc-bs=Ɂik ʈʰuʔ}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}} '''Yin Wood Ox also known as Kinoto-Ushi''' (乙丑, きのとうし, おつぼくのうし, いっちゅう) is one of the combinations of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
It is the second combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Wood Rat|ja|甲子|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Fire Tiger|ja|丙寅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}}乙 represents Yin Wood, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a relationship of {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=conquest|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Wood conquers Earth).
It is the second in the cycle, preceded by [[甲子]] (Kinoe-ne) and followed by [[丙寅]] (Hinoe-tora). In the [[Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory]], the [[Heavenly Stem]] [[乙]] represents the yin aspect of [[Wood]], while the [[Earthly Branch]] [[丑]] represents the yin aspect of [[Earth]]. This results in a [[Mutual Conquest]] relationship ([[Wood Conquers Earth]]).
== Years of Kinoto-Ushi == Gregorian calendar years that leave a remainder of 5 when divided by 60 are years of Kinoto-Ushi.
{| class="wikitable" |+'''Years of Kinoto-Ushi''' |- ! [[1st Millennium]] !! [[2nd Millennium]] !! [[3rd Millennium]] |- | * [[5]] * [[65]] * [[125]] * [[185]] * [[245]] * [[305]] * [[365]] * [[425]] {{citation needed|Wood Ox}}
* [[485]] * [[545]] * [[605]] * [[665]] * [[725]] * [[785]] * [[845]] * [[905]] * [[965]] | * [[1025]] * [[1085]] * [[1145]] * [[1205]] * [[1265]] * [[1325]] * [[1385]] * [[1445]] * [[1505]] * [[1565]] * [[1625]] * [[1685]] * [[1745]] * [[1805]] * [[1865]] * [[1925]] * [[1985]] | * [[2045]] * [[2105]] * [[2165]] * [[2225]] * [[2285]] * [[2345]] * [[2405]] * [[2465]] * [[2525]] * [[2585]] * [[2645]] * [[2705]] * [[2765]] * [[2825]] * [[2885]] * [[2945]] |}
== Months of Kinoto-Ushi == The twelfth month (December) of Gregorian calendar years ending in 3 or 8 (Heavenly Stems 癸 or 戊) corresponds to Kinoto-Ushi months. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Solar terms|ja|二十四節気|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (from {{ill|Shōkan|ja|小寒|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the day before {{ill|Risshun|ja|立春|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) in traditional contexts.
== Days of Kinoto-Ushi == === Calendar Annotations === Days of Kinoto-Ushi are associated with the following annotations in the {{ill|Japanese calendar|ja|暦注下段|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: * {{ill|Kyoueibi|ja|凶会日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – applicable in the 3rd and 10th lunar months. * {{ill|Gokubi|ja|五墓日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – applies to individuals whose {{ill|Na-in|ja|納音|qq=draft|qq=draft}} corresponds to the Wood element. * {{ill|Shinkichinichi|ja|神吉日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – auspicious for spiritual matters. == See Also == * {{prefix}} * {{intitle}} {{citation needed|Wood Ox}}
{{citation needed|Wood Ox}}
