It is the second combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Wood Rat|ja|甲子|1=Yang Wood Rat|1=Yang Wood Rat|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood Rat|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood Rat|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Wood Rat|qq=}} and preceding {{ill|Fire Tiger|ja|丙寅|1=Yang Fire Tiger|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire Tiger|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire Tiger|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Fire Tiger|qq=}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|lt=Heavenly Stem|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}} {{ill|Kinoto (乙)|ja|乙|zh|乙|gan|乙|hak|Yet (thiên-kôn)|ja|Kinoto|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kinoto (乙)|vi|Ất|za|Iet (diengan)|zh-min-nan|It (Thian-kan)|zh-yue|乙|zh|乙|lt=Kinoto (乙)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoto (乙)|qq=}} represents [[Yin]] [[Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (木)|2=uk|3=Дерево (елемент)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=Mộc (Ngũ hành)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=மரம் (சீன மெய்யியல்)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (木)|Wood]], while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|lt=Earthly Branch|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}} [[Ox (zodiac)|Ox (丑)]] represents [[Yin]] [[Earth (wuxing)|zh|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)|Earth]], creating a relationship of {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=conquest|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=}} (Wood conquers Earth).
== Years of Kinoto-Ushi == Gregorian calendar years that leave a remainder of 5 when divided by 60 are years of Kinoto-Ushi.
{| class="wikitable" |+'''Years of Kinoto-Ushi''' |- ! [[1st Millennium]] !! [[2nd Millennium]] !! [[3rd Millennium]] |- | * [[5]] * [[65]] * [[125]] * [[185]] * [[245]] * [[305]] * [[365]] * [[425]]
* [[485]] * [[545]] * [[605]] * [[665]] * [[725]] * [[785]] * [[845]] * [[905]] * [[965]] | * [[1025]] * [[1085]] * [[1145]] * [[1205]] * [[1265]] * [[1325]] * [[1385]] * [[1445]] * [[1505]] * [[1565]] * [[1625]] * [[1685]] * [[1745]] * [[1805]] * [[1865]] * [[1925]] * [[1985]] | * [[2045]] * [[2105]] * [[2165]] * [[2225]] * [[2285]] * [[2345]] * [[2405]] * [[2465]] * [[2525]] * [[2585]] * [[2645]] * [[2705]] * [[2765]] * [[2825]] * [[2885]] * [[2945]] |}
== Months of Kinoto-Ushi == The twelfth month (December) of Gregorian calendar years ending in 3 or 8 (Heavenly Stems 癸 or 戊) corresponds to Kinoto-Ushi months. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or {{ill|Solar terms|ja|二十四節気|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Solar terms|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Solar terms|qq=}} (from {{ill|Shōkan|ja|小寒|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōkan|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōkan|qq=}} to the day before {{ill|Risshun|ja|立春|1=Lichun|lt=Risshun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Risshun|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Risshun|13=User:Immanuelle/Lichun|qq=}}) in traditional contexts.
== Days of Kinoto-Ushi == === Calendar Annotations === Days of Kinoto-Ushi are associated with the following annotations in the {{ill|Japanese calendar|ja|暦注下段|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese calendar|qq=}}: * {{ill|Kyoueibi|ja|凶会日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoueibi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoueibi|qq=}} – applicable in the 3rd and 10th lunar months. * {{ill|Gokubi|ja|五墓日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gokubi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gokubi|qq=}} – applies to individuals whose {{ill|Na-in|ja|納音|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na-in|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na-in|qq=}} corresponds to the Wood element. * {{ill|Shinkichinichi|ja|神吉日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkichinichi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkichinichi|qq=}} – auspicious for spiritual matters. == See Also == * {{prefix|qq=}} * {{intitle|qq=}}
