{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Wood Ox|kanji=乙丑|romaji=kinoto ushi|onyomi=otsuchū|p=yǐchǒu|w=i-ch'ou|mi=i²¹ ʈʂʰoʊ̯²¹|y=jyut6 cau2|j=jyut6 cau2|ci=jyt̚ tsʰɐu̯²|mc=ʔit tʂʰjuwX|oc-bs=Ɂik ʈʰuʔ|qq=}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}} '''Yin Wood Ox also known as Kinoto-Ushi''' (乙丑, きのとうし, おつぼくのうし, いっちゅう) is one of the combinations of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
It is the second combination in the cycle, following [[:en:Wood Rat|Yang Wood Rat]] and preceding {{ill|Fire Tiger|ja|丙寅|1=Yang Fire Tiger|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire Tiger|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire Tiger|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Fire Tiger|qq=}}. According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Heavenly Stem]] {{ill|Kinoto (乙)|ja|乙|zh|乙|gan|乙|hak|Yet (thiên-kôn)|ja|Kinoto|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kinoto (乙)|vi|Ất|za|Iet (diengan)|zh-min-nan|It (Thian-kan)|zh-yue|乙|zh|乙|lt=Kinoto (乙)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoto (乙)|qq=}} represents [[Yin]] {{ill|Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (木)|2=uk|3=Дерево (елемент)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=Mộc (Ngũ hành)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=மரம் (சீன மெய்யியல்)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (木)}}, while the [[:en:Earthly Branches|Earthly Branch]] [[Ox (zodiac)|Ox (丑)]] represents [[Yin]] {{ill|Earth (wuxing)|zh|Earth (土)|comment=doing this to prevent wrong interwiki linking by bot|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|1=Earth (wuxing)|lt=Earth (土)|2=ru|3=Земля (у-син)|4=mn|5=Шороо (махбод)|6=uk|7=Земля (У-сін)|8=als|9=Ärde in dr chinesische Fümf-Elemänt-Leer|10=bcl|11=Daga (wuxing)|12=vi|13=Thổ (Ngũ hành)|lt=Earth (土)}}, creating a relationship of {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=conquest|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=}} (Wood conquers Earth).
==Pronunciation== * English: Yin Wood Ox (乙丑) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): yǐchǒu ** Cantonese (Jyutping): jyut3 cau2 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi 1: Kinoto-ushi ***Kunyomi 2: Otsuboku-no-ushi ***Onyomi 1: itchū ** Korean (Revised Romanization, Hangul): eulchuk (을축) ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Ất Sửu
<!-- == * Yin Wood Ox (乙丑) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): yǐchǒu ** Cantonese (Jyutping): jat1 cau2 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi: きのとうし (kinoto-ushi) ***Onyomi: おつぼくのうし (otsuboku-no-ushi) ***Onyomi: おつちゅう (otsuchū) ** Korean (Revised Romanization): eulchuk ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Ất Sửu
--> ==Years of Yin Wood Ox== Gregorian calendar years that leave a remainder of 5 when divided by 60 are years of Kinoto-Ushi.
{| class="wikitable" |+'''Years of Kinoto-Ushi''' |- ! [[:en:1st Millennium|1st Millennium]] !! [[2nd Millennium]] !! [[3rd Millennium]] |- | * [[5]] * [[65]] * [[:en:125|125]] * [[:en:185|185]] * [[245]] * [[305]] * [[365]] * [[425]]
* [[485]] * [[545]] * [[605]] * [[665]] * [[725]] * [[785]] * [[845]] * [[905]] * [[965]] | * [[:en:1025|1025]] * [[:en:1085|1085]] * [[:en:1145|1145]] * [[:en:1205|1205]] * [[:en:1265|1265]] * [[:en:1325|1325]] * [[:en:1385|1385]] * [[:en:1445|1445]] * [[:en:1505|1505]] * [[:en:1565|1565]] * [[:en:1625|1625]] * [[:en:1685|1685]] * [[:en:1745|1745]] * [[:en:1805|1805]] * [[:en:1865|1865]] * [[:en:1925|1925]] * [[:en:1985|1985]] | * [[:en:2045|2045]] * [[2105]] * [[2165]] * [[2225]] * [[2285]] * [[2345]] * [[2405]] * [[2465]] * [[2525]] * [[2585]] * [[2645]] * [[2705]] * [[2765]] * [[2825]] * [[2885]] * [[2945]] |}
==Months of Yin Wood Ox== The twelfth month (December) of Gregorian calendar years ending in 3 or 8 (Heavenly Stems 癸 or 戊) corresponds to Kinoto-Ushi months. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or [[:en:Solar term|Solar terms]] (from [[:en:Xiaohan|Shōkan]] to the day before [[:en:Lichun|Risshun]]) in traditional contexts.
==Days of Yin Wood Ox== === Rekichū === Days of Kinoto-Ushi are associated with the following annotations in the {{ill|Japanese calendar|ja|暦注下段|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese calendar|qq=}}: * {{ill|Kyoueibi|ja|凶会日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoueibi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoueibi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 暦注下段}} – applicable in the 3rd and 10th lunar months. * {{ill|Gokubi|ja|五墓日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gokubi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gokubi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 暦注下段}} – applies to individuals whose {{ill|Na-in|ja|納音|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na-in|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Na-in|qq=}} corresponds to the Wood element. * {{ill|Shinkichinichi|ja|神吉日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkichinichi|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkichinichi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 暦注下段}} – auspicious for spiritual matters. == See Also == * {{prefix|qq=}} * {{intitle|qq=}}
